paper joined the times 40 years ago and became letters editor in 
1979 
the best letters during his tenure pilpel said came during the 
falklands war with argentina in 1982 when former ambassadors and 
highlevel bureaucrats were moved to pick up their pens 
the letters columns he said have declined in influence 
the amount of information and the diversity of viewpoints 
made available to the public from every medium chiefly radio and 
