<TEXT>
greyhound lines inc on wednesday offered free bus 
trips through easter to passengers delayed on northeast routes in 
an effort to recapture business lost in the region during a 
monthlong drivers strike 
a suspicious fire broke out wednesday night in boston at a 
garage at a greyhound service terminal housing about 15 trailways 
buses fire officials said there were no injuries 
firefighters had to cut through a metal garage door to get to 
the fire and had a difficult time locating its source because the 
300 by 150foot garage was filled with smoke and heat said boston 
fire chief robert dillon the fire appeared to have been 
concentrated in a single bus trailways is owned by greyhound 
in new york city a state judge barred the company from hiring 
strikebreakers greyhound said it would appeal the ruling 
greyhounds 6300 drivers and about 3000 office and maintenance 
workers walked off the job march 2 in a dispute over wages and job 
security the countrys only nationwide bus company has operated on 
a reduced schedule since then using permanent replacements and 
union members who cross picket lines 
the union wednesday accused the company of allowing crazies 
and terrorists to block a resumption of talks the company 
called on the union to join in a news conference denouncing the 
violence and to cut strike benefits for union members who 
participate in attacks 
greyhound has said it will not bargain with the union until 
seven days have passed without shots being fired at one of its 
buses or facilities 
union spokesman nick nichols said the condition makes no sense 
they basically turned this whole process over to the people 
theyre calling the terrorists nichols said theres no way 
in my view that either the company or the union can control these 
crazies 
greyhound vice president p anthony lannie said in a letter to 
union president edward strait that absent implementation of 
effective measures to curb the illegal conduct the union cannot 
disclaim responsibility 
the unions conspicuous failure to implement effective 
measures against the violence lead to the inevitable conclusion of 
union responsibility for strike misconduct he said 
in new york judge diane lebedeff granted a union request for a 
temporary restraining order based on an antistrikebreaking statute 
passed by new yorks city council in 1962 but never used 
it prohibits a company for bringing in any workers for the 
purpose of having such person take the place in employment of 
employees in an industry or establishment where a strike or lockout 
exists 
the judge said greyhounds offer of a 2000 bonus to drivers 
hired during the strike tends to corroborate the charge that 
strikebreakers are being used 
greyhound spokesman george gravley said the ruling wouldnt 
affect the company much it does not interfere with our basic 
operations we dont hire strikebreakers he said 
dallasbased greyhound has been rebuilding its system since the 
strike began expanding mainly in the south and west 
last week company president frank schmieder said the walkout 
was essentially meaningless in much of the country however he 
acknowledged that the northeast which accounts for about 10 
percent of greyhound revenue remained a trouble spot 
greyhound said wednesday it was improving regional service by 
adding hourly departures on fridays and sundays from new york city 
to boston philadelphia and washington it guaranteed seats would 
be available and buses would run ontime 
we promise to arrive within 15 minutes of the scheduled 
arrival time schmieder said if we dont we will give our 
passengers a coupon good for a free round trip on the same route 
the guarantee covers albany buffalo rochester and syracuse 
ny boston montreal mount laurel nj philadelphia and 
washington is good only through easter sunday april 15 and must 
be redeemed by june 15 
greyhound spokeswoman elizabeth hale said the company had 
decided to focus attention on the northeast because of the regions 
level of commuter travel 
ms hale said 166 million people have taken greyhound buses 
since the strike began with 61437 traveling by bus on tuesday or 
468 percent of those who traveled on the same day last year 
percentages have been climbing slowly throughout the walkout 
greyhound has pledged not to resume negotiations with the 
amalgamated council of greyhound local unions until a week passes 
without major violence 
there have been 31 shootings including 26 at buses 70 bomb 
threats and more than 100 other incidents of violence greyhound 
officials say the union says about 60 of its pickets have been 
targets of violence a striker in redding calif was crushed to 
death march 3 by a bus being reversed by a replacement driver 
greyhound has offered a threeyear contract it values at 63 
million and says it can not afford to pay more the union says its 
own latest offer is worth about 40 million but greyhound says it 
would cost 180 million 
