kornblith led a team of physicians at montefiore medical center 
in new york city who implanted radioactive isotopes into the tumor 
tuesday in an effort to kill it 
mr atwater has done so well following this procedure that he 
will be able to be discharged from the hospital in a few days and 
may well be able to return to work in some degree within a couple 
of weeks said kornblith 
although it is obvious that this tumor is aggressive and 
dangerous mr atwater has many factors working in his favor 
said kornblith who cited the fact the party chairman is only 39 
and is in excellent health 
the tumor called an astrocytoma was described as the most 
common primary brain tumor 
it does not spread to other parts of the body but can cause 
damage to brain tissue by pressure and by invasion said 
kornblith 
a brain tumor undergoing unrestrained growth would cause 
pressure within the closed skull this pressure would kill normal 
brain cells thus bringing eventual death by destroying vital 
functions 
brain tumors can also spread by extension into other parts of 
the central nervous system and displace normal cells during such a 
process there would be a progressive loss of function as normal 
brain cells associated with memory thought muscle control and 
even heartbeat and respiration are lost 
in addition to the radiation treatment now underway the doctor 
said that to assure that any tumor cells peripheral to the main 
lesion are destroyed he will be receiving chemotherapy as well 
he said atwater would receive chemotherapy orally once every six 
weeks and it would not limit his activities or functions 
atwaters wife sally who is expecting their third child within 
days accompanied him to new york 
mary matalin gop chief of staff said atwater received numerous 
visitors wednesday but they had to stand behind a lead shield 
because of radioactivity 
kornblith said atwater will need to be followed closely and 
may need to have additional therapies in the future for the 
present we are delighted with his progress 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

