despite a federal appeals courts 
desegregation order lawyers for schools in kansas city and its 
suburbs are uncertain where more integrated education will result 
the order issued monday instructs a federal judge to draw up a 
plan for transferring students from mostly black innercity schools 
to the overwhelmingly white suburbs it orders the state to pay 
transportation costs and tuition for the students 
individual schools participation is voluntary however if they 
refuse there may be further litigation 
it would be a voluntary plan reg rowe a kansas city school 
district spokesman said this week however the language is very 
firm in the order concerning participation 
attorneys for the independence lees summit and north kansas 
city schools said their suburban districts may not be quick to 
participate 
if a district will take a thousand kids in the fall that 
would be satisfactory for all concerned said norman humphrey a 
lawyer representing the independence district but i dont know 
if any district can or would do that 
