<TEXT>
the un secretarygeneral and a brazilian 
who has fought to protect his countrys indian tribes and rain 
forests were among the winners thursday of the 1990 onassis awards 
the four prestigious awards honor international contributions in 
scholarship human rights and the environment 
javier perez de cuellar the secretarygeneral of the united 
nations received the main athinai prize for man and mankind in 
recognition of his personal initiative toward resolving worldwide 
crises 
premier xenophon zolotas handed out the awards during a ceremony 
in the nations former parliament building given by the alexander 
s onassis public benefit foundation each carries a prize of 
100000 
in his acceptance speech perez de cuellar said that in dealing 
with issues of international concern we too often lose sight of 
their human implications and moral dimension 
the other recipients were ailton krenak and the union of indian 
nations of brazil the city of warsaw poland and the goulandris 
natural history museum of greece 
in brief remarks new york university president john brademas 
said krenak is a resourceful courageous leader in the effort to 
protect the indigenous peoples of the amazon region of brazil and 
the rain forests that are your homes 
brademas lauded krenak for training indians to develop and 
protect their culture lands and other natural resources essential 
to the survival of the native people and of the forests they 
inhabit 
krenak speaking in portuguese accused international 
organizations including the world bank and the european community 
of ignoring the 300000 amazon indians when they sponsored a 
worldwide campaign to integrate the amazon to the international 
market and the modern economy 
in the amazon today krenak said you find farmers burning 
ecological reserves gold miners extracting gold from indian areas 
indians kicked out into the cities rubber tappers living in the 
slum peripheries and governments implementing damn roads and 
railroads in the middle of the forest 
what you do not see at all is a program directed to the 
population a program that admits that human beings exist said 
krenak whose family name is that of his indian tribe 
stanislaw wyganowski accepted the aristotelis prize for man and 
culture on behalf of the city of warsaw 
the polish capital was given the prize because of its 
exemplary restoration after its destruction during world war ii 
angelos and niki goulandris accepted the delphi prize for man 
and his environment on behalf of the goulandris natural history 
museum in the athens suburb of kifisia 
the onassis foundation was set up in 1975 by the estate of the 
late greek shipping tycoon aristotle s onassis in memory of his 
only son who was killed in a plane crash two years earlier 
