at least 659 people were killed in 
the first three months of 1990 in violence resulting from the 
nations communist insurgency the military chief said thursday 
armed forces chief gen renato de villa said that from january 
to march 365 communist rebels 179 soldiers and 115 civilians were 
killed in ambushes or clashes 
in the latest incident rebels shot to death an army captain and 
wounded his wife in a manila suburb thursday officials said 
they identified the officer as capt leodegario regis and said 
he was commanding officer of the capital commands long range unit 
an elite weapons and tactics team 
military authorities blamed communist assassins for the killing 
of about 30 soldiers and officials in the capital this year 
on wednesday communist rebels ambushed and killed nine troops 
on mindanao island 640 miles southeast of manila an army report 
said thursday 
one guerrilla was also killed in the attack and three rebels 
and two government soldiers were wounded the report said 
the rebels who have been fighting for 21 years to establish a 
communist state have threatened to intensify operations in urban 
centers including manila 
in another development the military said thursday that a 
lieutenant colonel sentenced to 12 years in prison for trying to 
topple president corazon aquino had escaped 
air force officials said imprisoned lt col rodolfo calzado 
never returned after he was permitted a temporary leave from a 
manila stockade feb 25 
officials did not say why he was allowed to leave 
