de klerk and mandela freed feb 11 by the president after 27 
years in prison met for three hours but said the time and place 
for talks to replace a canceled april 11 meeting would be announced 
later the two did not appear together afterwards 
instead at separate news conferences de klerk said he objected 
to the anc pressuring some tribal homeland leaders not to meet with 
the government earlier thursday while mandela said nothing could 
be further from the truth than charges of anc intimidation 
