<TEXT>
billed as slightly twisted and preceded by 
enough hype to fill a railroad hopper car david lynchs twin 
peaks a cuttingedge soap opera for prime time will open sunday 
on abc with a twohour premiere 
admirers of his cinematic oeuvre oeuvre is french for whole 
bunch of stuff may say peaks has subhematomal echoes of his 
neonoir blue velvet but not the nonlinear grecoroman 
postmodernism of eraserhead 
well okay some critics do talk that way 
but gee this series which starts its regular thursday run next 
week really seems more like a beautifully filmed pacific northwest 
edition of peyton place set in avantgarde mist 
full of slightly askew moments and characters it also is rife 
with little visual bumps to tip you that things are not always what 
they seem its an admirable effort to battle cable by offering 
something different in network tv 
abc deserves a cheer for that but sundays premiere directed 
and cowritten by lynch occasionally edges close to plumb boring 
at times you fear there has been a ruling that the director not 
the play is the thing 
the proceedings occur in washington near the canadian border 
in a small makebelieve logging town called twin peaks this 
hamlet surrounded by lovely cloudshrouded woods appears to be 
nice peaceful normal 
but all that starts changing early on when a fisherman 
discovers the plasticwrapped body of a slain high school 
homecoming queen naturally her nogood leatherjacketed 
boyfriend is a prime suspect 
unlike the usual tv epic the shows early moments contain 
leisurely digressions and characters that arent firmly and 
immediately established thats not all bad but it wears thin 
after awhile 
one gets a tad impatient waiting for things to get moving and 
for the stylistic fog to lift just a little 
those who wait and they should bring lunch eventually will 
learn that there is a killer at large apparently a sadist and 
rapist who preys on high school girls a serial killer maybe or 
maybe not ominous ambiguity is a major part of the proceedings 
bit by bit you learn that twin peaks is full of dark secrets 
subplots and furtive sex between consenting adults high school 
kids or a combination thereof but thats not enough nowadays 
so by golly theres also surrealism here although its the 
lowkey kind nothing really far out for example nobody suddenly 
up and shoots his mornings wheaties too bad that would give the 
show a cereal killer 
on the bright side there is a sheriffs deputy who cries every 
time hes at a murder scene also a derangedlooking psychiatrist 
who laughs about his dark secret and a group of potential land 
investors from norway 
there also is a lovely mysterious chinese woman she has what 
seems to be a light secret not so two townsfolk one a brutalized 
minor the other a trucker they prove to be advertisers in a 
swingers magazine 
this being the tv version of lynchs auteur theory there are 
various examples of his celebrated eccentric vision like a 
nighttime shot of a traffic light changing from green to amber to 
red hmm symbolic 
other auteur highlights a bad rich girls feet in saddle shoes 
a flickering light in a morgue and a dreamlike fight in a biker 
bar as a softrock vocalist gently sings 
meanwhile back at the plot the main event is an investigation 
of two things the homecoming queens murder and the rape and 
attempted murder of another high school girl 
the investigators here are sheriff harry s truman of course 
and fbi agent dale cooper played by michael ontkean and blue 
velvet graduate kyle maclachlan respectively 
the sheriff is the strong calm type the young razorsharp 
agent is a tad weird amazed at all the douglas firs he sees and 
constantly dictating all manner of things into his tape recorder 
included a misquote of wc fields 
ontkean and maclachlan are firstrate in fact all the actors 
in twin peaks are good 
but the only thing that truly keeps the show interesting is 
angelo badalamentis alwaysmoving score its a solid plus even 
though mostly played on a synthesizer a machine that is to music 
what helium is to combustion 
because of all the hoopla about twin peaks the show 
doubtless will get a large curious audience at least in its 
first hour on opening night 
but unless thursdays continuation of the plot is an improvement 
over chapter one the series that began as a rare network display 
of avantgarde may soon wind up as a video museum piece 
</TEXT>
