groundbreaking for the towers now is targeted for early next year 
on thursday the state court of appeals refused to hear a suit 
by wilder that sought further review of the project under state 
environmental guidelines 
kell predicted his side also would win two final lawsuits within 
a few months 
one a suit against the metropolitan transportation authority 
before the state court of appeals concerns bidding procedures for 
times square subway reconstruction in the other before a federal 
court a realty company is trying to stop the project on grounds 
among others that it lacks a public purpose 
