foreign brokers who had a hard time riding the 
bulls on the tokyo stock market are wrestling the bears with 
greater success 
nearly all the 50odd foreign brokerages in tokyo reported 
losing money during the late 1980s the 22 with seats on the tokyo 
stock exchange paid huge sums to get there and the others faced 
vast startup costs as well as of march 1988 for example 14 of 
the top 20 foreign houses were in the red 
but having absorbed the onetime expenses and gained market 
experience many are wellpositioned to capitalize on a plunging 
