<TEXT>
share prices finished slightly higher thursday 
after a lackluster session on londons stock exchange 
investors were content to sit on the sidelines waiting for a 
new trading account to begin friday afternoon traders said the 
exchange divides trading into twoweek and threeweek periods for 
accounting purposes 
traders said investors still were considering the ramifications 
of the tokyo markets gyrations 
players havent got a clear picture of whats happening in 
tokyo so theyre saying theyd rather not risk the money said a 
chief dealer 
wall street offered the london market little leadership with 
the dow jones average of 30 industrials up just a few points as 
london trading came to a close 
the financial timesstock exchange 100share index was up 79 
points or 04 percent at 22395 at the close its best level for 
the session and well above its low of 22220 
the financial times 30share index was up 66 points at 17563 
at the close the financial times 500share index rose 351 points 
to close at 120928 
volume was a moderate 4995 million shares down from 5054 
million on wednesday 
