avon products inc which late last month 
reached a truce with the investor group chartwell associates lp 
said thursday that chartwells recent additional purchases of its 
stock were inappropriate 
the avon board responded to chartwells stock purchases by 
voting thursday to amend the cosmetics companys share rights 
antitakeover plan the change essentially is meant to discourage 
chartwell from buying more avon stock 
the amendment lowers the threshold at which an element of the 
rights plan becomes effective it will apply when anyone acquires 
more than 125 percent of avons outstanding voting stock rather 
than 20 percent 
chartwell had said earlier in a filing to the securities and 
exchange commission that it raised its stake in avons common stock 
to 16 percent its holding of avons voting stock expanded to about 
12 percent 
the group which includes affiliates of mary kay corp oil heir 
gordon getty and the fisher real estate family of new york said it 
bought more than 345 million shares of avon common stock between 
march 27 and april 4 increasing its total holding to 905 million 
the partnership said it has spent more than 312 million from 
working capital to acquire its avon interest 
avon said in a letter to chartwell that the purchases could 
interfere with an agreement under which avon plans to nominate two 
chartwell candidates to its board at its annual meeting may 3 in 
return for the board seats chartwell had agreed to drop its proxy 
fight to win four seats on avons board of directors 
under the settlement the avon directors are establishing a 
committee to consider ways of boosting value for avon stockholders 
members of the special panel will be james e preston avons 
chairman and chief executive officer three incumbent members of 
the avon board and the two chartwell nominees 
the panel will examine alternatives to maximize value such as a 
recapitalization asset sales an outright sale of avon or a 
leveraged buyout 
preston said in the letter that the board is concerned 
chartwells new purchases will prejudice the ability of the 
special committee to consider all the alternatives in carrying 
out its assigned task 
in addition the board believes that such purchases will have 
adverse consequences on our operating businesses and could be 
unfair to other shareholders preston said 
the letter was sent to richard fisher a member of chartwell it 
was released by avons headquarters in new york 
